com.instil.lgi
Class ParsingGrammar

java.lang.Object
  com.instil.lgi.ParsingGrammar
Direct Known Subclasses:
ParsingExpressionGrammar
public class ParsingGrammar
extends java.lang.Object

This class contains all the information related to a generated grammar. It mainly provides methods to check the validity of the grammar tree, and to query for Patterns (regular expressions) used to match lexical tokens. It also provides look-up methods for types and names of Blocks.

The Block trees containing a grammar description must have the following structure after optimizing them 

                  G
                  |
        --------------------
        |        |   ...   |
        D        D   ...   D
        |        |   ...   |
      ------  ------    ------
      |  | |  |  | |    |  | |
      I <- E  I <- E    I <- E
Where G stands for the grammar tree root, D is a description Block, I is an identifier acting as the rule name, <- is the lexical token corresponding to an assignment, and E corresponds to the expression describing the contents of the description.

Author:
Edgar A. Duenez-Guzman

See Also:
ParsingGrammar( Block, boolean )

ParsingGrammar

public ParsingGrammar(Block grammar,
                      boolean optimize)
Creates a new instance of ParsingGrammar given the specified Block tree and the optimize flag.

If the value of optimize is true, then this Block tree MUST have the topology dicussed before. Otherwise, a call to PEGUtility.utility.optimizeParsedTree( grammar ) is performed before processing the grammar.

This class assigns numerical types in the order of definition of the Blocks. Thus, the first definition will be of type zero, the next of type one and so on.

Parameters:
grammar - The Block tree containing the grammar description.
optimize - If true, the tree will be optimized prior to processing.
See Also:
PEGUtility

addLiteral

public void addLiteral(java.lang.String literal)
This method allows for post-generation addition of literals (Patterns). It re-sorts the literals to accomodate the addition and thus calling this method should not be abused.

Parameters:
literal - The literal to add to the grammar.
